                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bowen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay states that all the powers seem inclined to accept the principle of
                    arbitration; that the Government of the United States think the selection of The
                    Hague tribunal would be judicious, with the reservation of certain questions
                    which might be settled directly, and that no reply has been received to the
                    suggestion of Mr. Bowen’s name as plenipotentiary of Venezuela.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
